DESCRIPTION:Welcome to SHG's North End weekly parkday group! We meet every 
	Wednesday during the school year\, rain or shine\, at St. Edward State Par
	k. The play is unstructured and child-led\, and often includes large field
	 games like capture the flag or freeze tag\, or smaller groups adventuring
	 around the large playground together. All homeschool ages are welcome\, a
	nd our current age ranges are usually 5 to 16.  Because it is a state park
	\, the parking lot requires a yearly Discover Pass\, or a day pass. Annual
	 passes will be increasing from $30 to $45 on October 1st. We want park da
	y to be accessible for all homeschoolers\, so if parking costs is a barrie
	r\, please contact Christine Jones for options. More information on the pa
	rk can be found here: https://parks.wa.gov/find-parks/state-parks/saint-ed
	ward-state-park Parking passes can be found here: https://store.discoverpa
	ss.wa.gov\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/north-end-shg-p
	ark-day/18291039/2026-03-11T00
